# TypeScript Rules

Always use

Strict TypeScript.

## Forbidden

any

enum

magic strings

magic numbers

non-null assertions unless justified

implicit any

console.log

## Required

readonly where appropriate

discriminated unions

explicit return types for public APIs

small interfaces

typed IPC

Use Zod for runtime validation.

Never duplicate interfaces.

Extract reusable types.

No business logic in components.

Avoid classes unless necessary.

Prefer functions.
